<br>
No disrespect intended but have even played a low lvl character lately?<br>
<br>
A lvl 20 warrior with a fungi venom axe and frostbringer with a few peices of cobalt is going to WAY OUTPERFORM a lvl 20 mage with FBCR, heiro cloak, cone of mystics, golden bracer, etc.<br>
<br>
It has nothing to do with skill - It has to do with this warrior regening massive HP while dishing out massive damage.  The lvl 20 mage can use every ounce of skill but his damage output is going to be the same - since his spells are still lvl 20 and his pet lvl has not improved for 2 years.  He might have a few hundred extra mana, a few extra HP but it certainly doesnt put him in the same bracket with the lvl 20 warrior.  I mean seriously - this warrior is procin a 86dd from lvl 1 - c'mon...<br>
<br>
At the high end game, we have all noticed the decline of the caster population - in particular pet casters - in favor of melee twinks that have now reached lvl 60.  A few token spells certainly aren't going to bring them back.<br>
<br>
EDIT:<br>
